**[1847, 02-7] Ms.A.1.2.9.11**

Ashurst to WLG

Solicits article for *People’s Journal*, saying anything from Garrison’s
pen on slavery would probably be gladly received. “The People’s Journal
belonging to a Mr Saunders circulates very largely (20 or 25,000)
amongst our reading Middle class.” If Garrisons ever wish to come to
England as a couple, he would welcome them.


